    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Motif of an almond-shape with a circle in the middle, representing a human eye seen frontally. It was first used in Ancient Egypt; generally was a symbol of protection and power.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
